rich_zig.StyleAttribute;\n\n/// Style represents visual attributes for text cells.\n///\n/// Wraps rich_zig.Style with zithril-specific conveniences.\n/// Supports:\n/// - Foreground and background inner: rich_zig.Style,\n\n    /// Empty style with all defaults.\n    pub const empty: Style = .{ .inner = rich_zig.Style.empty };\n\n    /// Initialize an empty style.\n    pub fn init() Style {\n        return empty;\n    }\n\n    /// Set foreground color.\n    pub fn fg(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.fg(c) };\n    }\n\n    /// Set foreground color (alias for fg).\n    pub fn foreground(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return self.fg(c);\n    }\n\n    /// Set background color.\n    pub fn bg(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.bg(c) };\n    }\n\n    /// Set background color (alias for bg).\n    pub fn background(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return self.bg(c);\n    }\n\n    /// Enable bold.\n    pub fn bold(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.bold() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable bold.\n    pub fn notBold(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notBold() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable italic.\n    pub fn italic(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.italic() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable italic.\n    pub fn notItalic(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notItalic() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable underline.\n    pub fn underline(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.underline() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable underline.\n    pub fn notUnderline(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notUnderline() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable dim.\n    pub fn dim(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.dim() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable dim.\n    pub fn notDim(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notDim() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable blink.\n    pub fn blink(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.blink() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable blink.\n    pub fn notBlink(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notBlink() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable reverse video.\n    pub fn reverse(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.reverse() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable reverse video.\n    pub fn notReverse(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notReverse() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable strikethrough.\n    pub fn strikethrough(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.strikethrough() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable strikethrough.\n    pub fn notStrikethrough(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notStrike() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable strikethrough (alias).\n    pub fn strike(self: Style) Style {\n        return self.strikethrough();\n    }\n\n    /// Merge another style on top of this one.\n    /// Non-default values in `other` override values in `self`.\n    pub fn patch(self: Style, other: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.combine(other.inner) };\n    }\n\n    /// Create from a rich_zig style.\n    pub fn fromRichStyle(rich_style: rich_zig.Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = rich_style };\n    }\n};\n\n// Coordinates increase right and down.\npub const Rect = struct {\n    x: u16,\n    y: u16,\n    width: u16,\n    height: u16,\n\n    pub fn init(x: u16, y: u16, width: u16, height: u16) Rect {\n        return .{ .x = x, .y = y, .width = width, .height = height };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns a new Rect inset by `margin` on all sides.\n    /// Uses saturating subtraction to prevent underflow.\n    /// Position shifts inward; dimensions shrink by 2*margin (or to zero).\n    pub fn inner(self: Rect, margin: u16) Rect {\n        const double_margin = @as(u32, margin) * 2;\n\n        return .{\n            .x = self.x +| margin,\n            .y = self.y +| margin,\n            .width = if (double_margin >= self.width) 0 else self.width - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n            .height = if (double_margin >= self.height) 0 else self.height - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns area (width * height) as u32 to prevent overflow.\n    pub fn area(self: Rect) u32 {\n        return @as(u32, self.width) * @as(u32, self.height);\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if rect has zero area.\n    pub fn isEmpty(self: Rect) bool {\n        return self.width == 0 or self.height == 0;\n    }\n\n    /// Clamp a point to be within this rect (inclusive of boundaries).\n    /// Returns the closest point inside the rect.\n    pub fn clamp(self: Rect, x: u16, y: u16) Position {\n        const max_x = self.x +| (self.width -| 1);\n        const max_y = self.y +| (self.height -| 1);\n\n        return .{\n            .x = std.math.clamp(x, self.x, max_x),\n            .y = std.math.clamp(y, self.y, max_y),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the right edge x coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn right(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.x +| self.width;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the bottom edge y coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn bottom(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.y +| self.height;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if the given point is within this rect (inclusive).\n    pub fn contains(self: Rect, x: u16, y: u16) bool {\n        return x >= self.x and\n            x < self.right() and\n            y >= self.y and\n            y < self.bottom();\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// 24,\n    color_system: ColorSystem = .standard,\n    is_tty: bool = false,\n    supports_unicode: bool = true,\n    supports_hyperlinks: bool = false,\n    term: ?[]const u8 = null,\n    term_program: ?[]const u8 = null,\n};\n\nconst TerminalSize = struct { width: u16, height: u16 };\n\npub fn detect() TerminalInfo {\n    var info = TerminalInfo{};\n\n    // Get environment variables (cross-platform)\n    info.term = std.process.getEnvVarOwned(std.heap.page_allocator, \"TERM\") catch null;\n    info.term_program = std.process.getEnvVarOwned(std.heap.page_allocator, \"TERM_PROGRAM\") catch null;\n\n    // Check if stdout is a TTY\n    info.is_tty = isTty();\n\n    if (!info.is_tty) {\n        // Check FORCE_COLOR\n        if (getEnv(\"FORCE_COLOR\")) |_| {\n            info.color_system = .truecolor;\n        } else {\n            info.color_system = .standard;\n        }\n        return info;\n    }\n\n    // Get terminal size\n    const size = getTerminalSize();\n    info.width = size.width;\n    info.height = size.height;\n\n    // Detect color support\n    if (getEnv(\"NO_COLOR\")) |_| {\n        info.color_system = .standard;\n    } else {\n        info.color_system = detectColorSystem();\n    }\n\n    // Detect hyperlink support\n    info.supports_hyperlinks = detectHyperlinks();\n\n    return info;\n}\n\nfn isTty() bool {\n    if (builtin.os.tag == .windows) {\n        const handle = std.os.windows.GetStdHandle(std.os.windows.STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE) catch return false;\n        var mode: std.os.windows.DWORD = 0;\n        return std.os.windows.kernel32.GetConsoleMode(handle, &mode) != 0;\n    } else {\n        const fd = std.posix.STDOUT_FILENO;\n        return std.posix.isatty(fd);\n    }\n}\n\nfn getEnv(name: []const u8) ?[]const u8 {\n    return std.process.getEnvVarOwned(std.heap.page_allocator, name) catch null;\n}\n\nfn getTerminalSize() TerminalSize {\n    if (builtin.os.tag == .windows) {\n        return getTerminalSizeWindows();\n    } else if (builtin.os.tag == .wasi or builtin.cpu.arch == .wasm32) {\n        return .{ .width = 80, .height = 24 };\n    } else {\n        return getTerminalSizePosix();\n    }\n}\n\nfn getTerminalSizeWindows() TerminalSize {\n    const handle = std.os.windows.GetStdHandle(std.os.windows.STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE) catch\n        return .{ .width = 80, .height = 24 };\n\n    var info: std.os.windows.CONSOLE_SCREEN_BUFFER_INFO = undefined;\n    if (std.os.windows.kernel32.GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo(handle, &info) != 0) {\n        const width: u16 = @intCast(info.srWindow.Right - info.srWindow.Left + 1);\n        const height: u16 = @intCast(info.srWindow.Bottom - info.srWindow.Top + 1);\n        return .{ .width = width, .height = height };\n    }\n\n    return .{ .width = 80, .height = 24 };\n}\n\nfn getTerminalSizePosix() TerminalSize {\n    if (@hasDecl(std.posix, \"winsize\")) {\n        var ws: std.posix.winsize = undefined;\n        const result = std.posix.system.ioctl(std.posix.STDOUT_FILENO, std.posix.T.IOCGWINSZ, @intFromPtr(&ws));\n        if (result == 0) {\n            return .{ .width = ws.col, .height = ws.row };\n        }\n    }\n    return .{ .width = 80, .height = 24 };\n}\n\nfn detectColorSystem() ColorSystem {\n    // Check COLORTERM\n    if (getEnv(\"COLORTERM\")) |ct| {\n        defer std.heap.page_allocator.free(ct);\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, ct, \"truecolor\") or std.mem.eql(u8, ct, \"24bit\")) {\n            return .truecolor;\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Check TERM\n    if (getEnv(\"TERM\")) |term| {\n        defer std.heap.page_allocator.free(term);\n        if (std.mem.indexOf(u8, term, \"256color\") != null or\n            std.mem.indexOf(u8, term, \"256\") != null)\n        {\n            return .eight_bit;\n        }\n        if (std.mem.indexOf(u8, term, \"truecolor\") != null) {\n            return .truecolor;\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Check terminal program\n    if (getEnv(\"TERM_PROGRAM\")) |prog| {\n        defer std.heap.page_allocator.free(prog);\n        const truecolor_terminals = [_][]const u8{\n            \"iTerm.app\",\n            \"Apple_Terminal\",\n            \"WezTerm\",\n            \"vscode\",\n            \"Hyper\",\n            \"mintty\",\n            \"Terminus\",\n            \"Alacritty\",\n            \"kitty\",\n        };\n        for (truecolor_terminals) |t| {\n            if (std.mem.eql(u8, prog, t)) return .truecolor;\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Windows Terminal\n    if (getEnv(\"WT_SESSION\")) |wt| {\n        defer std.heap.page_allocator.free(wt);\n        return .truecolor;\n    }\n\n    // ConEmu\n    if (getEnv(\"ConEmuANSI\")) |ce| {\n        defer std.heap.page_allocator.free(ce);\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, ce, \"ON\")) {\n            return .truecolor;\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Default for modern terminals\n    return .eight_bit;\n}\n\nfn detectHyperlinks() bool {\n    // OSC 8 hyperlink support detection\n    if (getEnv(\"TERM_PROGRAM\")) |prog| {\n        defer std.heap.page_allocator.free(prog);\n        const supported = [_][]const u8{\n            \"iTerm.app\",\n            \"WezTerm\",\n            \"vscode\",\n            \"Hyper\",\n            \"Alacritty\",\n            \"kitty\",\n        };\n        for (supported) |t| {\n            if (std.mem.eql(u8, prog, t)) return true;\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Windows Terminal supports hyperlinks\n    if (getEnv(\"WT_SESSION\")) |wt| {\n        defer std.heap.page_allocator.free(wt);\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    return false;\n}\n\npub fn enableVirtualTerminal() bool {\n    if (builtin.os.tag == .windows) {\n        const handle = std.os.windows.GetStdHandle(std.os.windows.STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE) catch Cell type for zithril TUI framework\n// Represents a single character cell in the terminal buffer\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\npub const rich_zig = @import(\"rich_zig\");\nconst style_mod = @import(\"style.zig\");\npub const Style = style_mod.Style;\n\n/// A single cell in the terminal buffer.\n/// Each cell represents one character position, with its associated style and display width.\npub const Cell = struct {\n    /// Unicode codepoint for the character displayed in this cell.\n    /// Defaults to space (U+0020).\n    char: u21 = ' ',\n\n    /// Visual style applied to this cell (colors, bold, italic, etc).\n    style: Style = Style.empty,\n\n    /// Display width in terminal columns.\n    /// - 1 for most characters (ASCII, basic Latin, etc.)\n    /// - 2 for wide characters (CJK ideographs, emoji, fullwidth forms)\n    /// - 0 for combining marks (handled specially during rendering)\n    width: u8 = 1,\n\n    /// The default cell: a space with default style and width 1.\n    pub const default: Cell = .{};\n\n    /// Create a cell with a specific character, using default style.\n    pub fn init(char: u21) Cell {\n        return .{\n            .char = char,\n            .style = Style.empty,\n            .width = charWidth(char),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a cell with a character and style.\n    pub fn styled(char: u21, s: Style) Cell {\n        return .{\n            .char = char,\n            .style = s,\n            .width = charWidth(char),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a cell with explicit width override.\n    pub fn withWidth(char: u21, s: Style, w: u8) Cell {\n        return .{\n            .char = char,\n            .style = s,\n            .width = w,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Update the cell's character, automatically recalculating width.\n    pub fn setChar(self: Cell, char: u21) Cell {\n        return .{\n            .char = char,\n            .style = self.style,\n            .width = charWidth(char),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Update the cell's style.\n    pub fn setStyle(self: Cell, s: Style) Cell {\n        return .{\n            .char = self.char,\n            .style = s,\n            .width = self.width,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Merge another style on top of this cell's style.\n    pub fn patchStyle(self: Cell, s: Style) Cell {\n        return .{\n            .char = self.char,\n            .style = self.style.patch(s),\n            .width = self.width,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this cell is the default (space with empty style).\n    pub fn isDefault(self: Cell) bool {\n        return self.char == ' ' and self.style.isEmpty() and self.width == 1;\n    }\n\n    /// Check equality with another cell.\n    pub fn eql(self: Cell, other: Cell) bool {\n        return self.char == other.char and\n            self.style.eql(other.style) and\n            self.width == other.width;\n    }\n\n    /// Get the character width using rich_zig's cell width calculation.\n    /// Returns 1 for most chars, 2 for wide (CJK/emoji), 0 for combining.\n    pub fn charWidth(char: u21) u8 {\n        return rich_zig.cells.getCharacterCellSize(char);\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this cell contains a wide character (width 2).\n    pub fn isWide(self: Cell) bool {\n        return self.width == 2;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this cell contains a zero-width character (combining mark).\n    pub fn isZeroWidth(self: Cell) bool {\n        return self.width == 0;\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - std.testing.expect(cell.style.isEmpty());\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Cell.styled creates cell with style\" {\n    const s = Style.init().bold().fg(.red);\n    const cell = Cell.styled('X', s);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u21, 'X'), cell.char);\n    try std.testing.expect(cell.style.hasAttribute(.bold));\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// BEHAVIOR TESTS try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 2), updated.width);\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Cell.setStyle preserves char and width\" {\n    const cell = Cell.init(0x4E2D);\n    const styled_cell = self.writeEscape(ENABLE_BRACKETED_PASTE);\n        }\n\n        return self;\n    }\n\n    /// Restore terminal to original state.\n    /// Safe to call multiple times.\n    pub fn deinit(self:
